                        <div id="page-title">
                            Bring Light
                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        




<p>Many believe that there is evil in the world, and that is part of the apocalypse, the understanding that the evil is powerful, and has become organized against &quot;righteousness.&quot; My belief is that collectively, we must organize against it, and attempt to make the world around us a better place. What I see, is that pretty much everyone gives up, decides they alone cannot make the world a better place, and basically sits down on the sideline to watch the carnage of Satan's army destroying our once free and proud civilization.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“There is a <em>power so organized, so subtle, so watchful, so interlocked, so complete, so pervasive</em> that prudent men better not speak above their breath when they speak in condemnation of it.”</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Woodrow T. Wilson</p>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="toc0"><span>Speak loudly and do it quickly, it's time.</span></h2>
<p>The most important part of what I just said is that evil is now organized, it's so organized in fact, that it's effectively the best intelligence agency on the planet. That does sound dismal, when you really think about it. Faced with an enemy like that, without a significantly larger opposing force (assuming a secular battle) we are all bu doomed without outside assistance. While I'm aware that assistance is promised, and it may very well be coming; there must be an alternative to each individual giving up on their ideals and beliefs. Goodness should be recognized and rewarded, and we should be attempting to unite against it.</p>
<h2 id="toc1"><span>Be good. For yourself, and for everyone else.</span></h2>
<p>Even if winning isn't possible right now, or organizing to the same level is not&#8230; still sitting down on the sidelines is the wrong thing to do. Everyone needs to chip in, and donate a little bit of goodness to the collective of humanity. In the here and now, that amounts to not remaining silent when you see injustice and evil. It amounts to standing up for the right thing, whenever you possibly can.</p>
<p>Certainly, what we all need to do is <em>not participate</em> in something that we know s wrong. It's an easy thing to say, but when it comes down to it, <em>witnessing an injustice</em> and failing to do <em>something</em> to make it better&#8230; is basically complicity. Don't be part of the problem.</p>
<p>What action is possible? How can we stop the systematic destruction of our liberty? How can we stop a government that wants to start a war so badly, it has the gaul to attack itself?</p>
<p>There must be an answer.</p>

                    </div>

                    


                    



                    

